## Priority: High

`IncrementalCompiler` (using mizchi/ripple) is already implemented. Cached compile returns in ~0.3µs for unchanged files. A file watcher completes the dev loop.

## Scope

- `watch <directory>` CLI command
- Polling-based change detection (read files, feed to `IncrementalCompiler.set_source`)
- Output compiled files: `<name>.client.mbt`, `<name>.server.mbt`, `<name>.css`
- Console output showing changed files and timing

## Dependencies

- Requires sleep/poll mechanism (C FFI `usleep` or busy-wait)
- `@fs.read_dir` for directory listing